    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="598" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Lothrop</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    in State.</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-06-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 119 of the 1st
                        instant, in which you send a paragraph and translation from the Journal de
                        St. Petersbourg relative to the proposed new Russian law of naturalization
                        which will permit Russian subjects to obtain naturalization abroad. This is
                        an encouraging sign.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
